I met Julie at my @own_the_stage_posing_workshop Mock Show earlier this year and a few months later she went on to win 1st place 2X at her very first show Iron Games in Masters 45 & 50 as well as 2nd place in True Novice & Novice. Congratulations on all your success Julie! So happy for you and proud of you ❤️❤️❤️ Got to answer some questions & share some of my back ground with Julie today including the story behind the shirt I’m wearing here that I wear so often. I made it and another one for the @arnoldsports (my last 2 shows before I retired as a competitor) for my athlete booth at the meet and greets as an honoring of God. 

This one says “All or Nothing” because that’s how I do it. I don’t believe in the Luke warm. Hot or Cold baby! It also has bible verse Corinthians 4:20 “for the kingdom of God is not a matter of talk, but of power” because that verse is everything and was at the forefront of my mind as I approached my last 2 shows. The 2nd T-shirt says “Victory in Jesus” because when we wake up to knowing the Christ light in ourselves we are victorious! Winners of the game called LIFE! 

Those are messages I believe in that I wanted to throw out to my audience. I gave Julie both T’s today since they resonated with her too. Much love Queen!

Tomorrow I will be officially 39 weeks and AJ will be full term. Expecting him any day now. So excited to meet my baby boy. This photo was at 34 weeks. He has grown about a half pound a week since week 32/33. I think he is about 7ish pounds now but in this photo about 5 pounds. 💕💕💕 

I stopped taking one on one clients beginning of July (about 36 weeks) which is better/longer than I planned. Online clients are still welcome. But definitely enjoying and embracing the very different lifestyle that is happening now. Getting all the baby things ready has been a lot of work and I’m so glad I took this last month off to focus on my final baby prep. I used to take 2 weeks off before all my IFBB Pro Shows to really focus on the task at hand and this is way more important. Whatever I do I like to give it my best. All or Nothing. I have applied so many things I learned through bodybuilding to my pregnancy. Affirmations, Meditation, Prayer, Focusing on my oneness with God & Life, Mindset, Training & Nutrition. It has been a very spiritual process just like my shows and just like anything I do. 

My husband and I have prepared for this by taking all classes the hospital had to offer, a separate Hypnobirthing Class, Lactation Consultant, Prenatal massages, Perineal Massage, Pelvic Floor Therapy & a bunch of research. So thankful to my man @atofaniman for making it to all the doctor appointments & all the support even with his extremely busy schedule. Love you baby. Excited to start our beautiful family. 

#34weekspregnant #34weeks

So grateful to have had this beautiful day with my closest friends in Long Beach last weekend. I love you guys so much and thank you for celebrating our last lunch out before the birth of our beautiful baby AJ. @atofaniman

“WHY NOT ME” was my mantra as I prepared my mind for the USAs 2013 where I won my IFBB Pro Card at my first National Bodybuilding Competition on the @musclecontest stage which became my home stage as I continued my career in Bikini Bodybuilding. “Why not me?” I started to ask myself. If not me then who, if not now then when? I’ve worked just as hard if not harder. I’m just as good if not better. I gave this show all I had mentally, physically, spiritually. 💯 To the point where I decided if I didn’t get my Pro card I would stop competing. This was my best to date at that time. No regrets. Laid it all down. Put so much of my self into this one that I was ready to walk away if I didn’t get what I came for. Just when you are ready to give up VICTORY is right around the corner. I know you have heard that before and it’s totally true. So keeping pushing to that point for anything you want or believe in and you will manifest it. 

Shout out to all the competitors that made it to the @musclecontest USA National Competition this weekend. You all are amazing for even getting to a stage like that. Your determination, discipline, focus & will power had to be stronger than most. Congratulations to you and to all the athletes that will achieve their IFBB pro status today. What an incredible feeling it is. I’m so happy for all of you. 👏👏👏 Keep up the FAITH!

Stepping on stage in Tahoe was something I never dreamed of doing if you asked me 7+ years ago. Last year, that all changed. When I became a mother, I was celebrating my new role, yet felt like I was mourning the loss of who I was before kids.

After having my boys, I wanted to get back into a healthier state - physically, mentally, and emotionally. With the help of my family 🤍, I was able to get back into the gym regularly. But I felt like that wasn’t challenging enough to get me where I wanted to be. September 2022 was when I reached out to my friend, and now coach, Gil. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m so damn proud that I can say “I did it… I did the damn thing.” Of course, I couldn’t have done it without the love and support from my husband, my family, my coach & teammates, my friends, and my gym community. I owe it to you all for believing in me and continuously pushing me. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I cannot thank everyone who personally reached out last weekend with your encouragement!! I don’t think you all know how meaningful that was to me!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It was my first show and we did come back with some hardware, some heavy ones might I add!!! 🤩
